title.narrative: National program on positive parenting is developed and modelled

description.narrative: A multisectoral positive parenting program responding to a key priority of the national ECD strategy was developed with UNICEF support and validated by national partners, including 5 Ministries involved in its governance. The programme is informed by comprehensive evidence gained through a country-wide survey on the knowledge, attitudes and practices (KAP) of parents of children aged 0-6 years, and is designed to be modelled in 4 regions of Tunisia in 2020. Promoting the nurturing care of young children, the programme covers interventions in early stimulation and education, health, nutrition and protection. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:21/01/2020
